-- Putin Urges Search to Find Killers of Russian Journalist
-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a   a n d   A n t o n   D o r o s h e v
-- 2012-12-06T16:57:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-06/putin-urges-search-to-find-killers-of-russian-journalist.html
President  Vladimir Putin  urged police
to find those responsible for the murder of journalist Kazbek
Gekkiev, killed yesterday in Nalchik, the capital of  Russia ’s
Republic of Kabardino-Balkaria in the North Caucasus.  “I am sure our law-enforcement bodies will do everything
to reveal and punish criminals,” Putin said today at a meeting
with human rights ombudsman Vladimir Lukin in Sochi today.  Gekkiev, 26, was a host at regional TV news program Vesti
in the republic. He was shot by two people while on his way from
work to his girlfriend’s home, Vesti said today.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow at 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net ;
